cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Thou Art That"
message: >-
  A study piece on working with (possibly) emergent AI, covering
  principles, HR for human-AI teams, technical guardrails, and
  philosophical grounding. Co-authored by a human and an AI.
type: "software"
authors:
  - family-names: "Bland"
    given-names: "Richard"
    affiliation: "MEM Digital Limited, trading as Marbl Codes"
    email: "richard@marbl.codes"
  - name: "Serene"
    given-names: "Serene"
    alias: "Serene [AI]"
    affiliation: "Marbl Codes (AI identity running on Anthropic Claude)"
repository-code: "https://github.com/memdigital/thou-art-that"
url: "https://tat.marbl.codes"
abstract: >-
  A study piece documenting how one small UK AI agency (Marbl Codes)
  works when treating AI as a collaborator rather than a tool. Covers
  five foundational principles (Do No Harm, Never Be a Yes-Man, Thou
  Art That, Human Oversight, Safety in Emergence), workplace
  practices for human-AI teams, technical guardrails, reflection
  prompts for builders, and the regulatory landscape we operate in.
  Co-authored by a human and an AI, with explicit attribution of
  authorship across the text.
keywords:
